fix(rtc): address Copilot review comments on PR #124

- GeneralTab: remove `devicechange` listener in onCleanup so the
  MicDeviceSelect doesn't leak handlers across mount cycles.
- useLivekitRoom.tryPlayAll: switch to Promise.allSettled so the
  blocked-audio flag actually reflects awaited play() rejections
  (was checked synchronously before catches ran). Returns a boolean
  so resumeAudio can gate the banner clear on success.
- useLivekitRoom: clear audioBlocked on Disconnected/teardown so a
  stale "Enable audio" banner can't outlive the call.
- useLivekitRoom.Disconnected: gate setStatus("idle") so an
  unsolicited disconnect doesn't clobber error/disconnecting state.
- useLivekitRoom.resumeAudio: only clear audioBlocked after at least
  one play() / startAudio() actually succeeds.
- useLivekitRoom: attempt-gate the async setAudioBlocked(true) sites
  (tryPlayAll, attachAudioTrack catch) so late-arriving rejections
  from a torn-down session can't resurrect the banner.
- fetchLivekitToken.normaliseJwtServiceUrl: parse with new URL(...)
  and normalise only pathname, preserving any ?query/#fragment.
  Recognise three shapes — full path, `${base}/livekit`, bare base —
  matching the convention written by discoverFoci.ts. Preserve any
  `/sfu/get` ending so non-Element-Call deployments aren't doubled.
- fetchLivekitToken.test: replace obsolete normalization test with
  two new cases covering the bare-base and `${base}/livekit` shapes.
- NativeCallView: add role="img" to the muted-state SVG for screen
  reader consistency with the rest of the app.

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
